import numpy as np

def normalize_pose(pose):
    norm_pose = np.zeros((7,))
    norm_pose[0:3] = pose[0:3]
    norm_pose[3] = np.cos(np.deg2rad(pose[3]))
    quaternion = pose[4:]
    norm_quaternion = quaternion * np.linalg.norm(quaternion)
    norm_pose[4:] = norm_quaternion
    return norm_pose
